# JavaScript Tooling

## Package Manager — bun

Use **bun** for all JavaScript and TypeScript projects. Never use bare `npm`, `yarn`, or `pnpm` for new projects.

```bash
# New project
bun init

# Install all dependencies (replaces npm install)
bun install

# Add a runtime dependency
bun add react vinext

# Add a dev dependency
bun add -D typescript @types/react

# Remove a dependency
bun remove lodash

# Run a script from package.json
bun run dev
bun run build

# Execute a package binary without installing (replaces npx)
bun x vinext init

# Run a file directly
bun run src/index.ts
```

`bun` manages dependencies, runs scripts, and executes TypeScript natively — no separate `ts-node` or `tsx` needed.

| Don't | Do instead |
|---|---|
| `npm install` | `bun install` |
| `npm install react` | `bun add react` |
| `npm install --save-dev jest` | `bun add -D jest` |
| `npm run dev` | `bun run dev` or `bun dev` |
| `npx create-next-app` | `bun x create-next-app` |
| `npm uninstall lodash` | `bun remove lodash` |

### Docker — cache bun's install cache across builds

```dockerfile
FROM oven/bun:1-alpine AS deps
WORKDIR /app
COPY package.json bun.lock ./
RUN --mount=type=cache,target=/root/.bun/install/cache \
    bun install --frozen-lockfile

FROM oven/bun:1-alpine AS builder
WORKDIR /app
COPY --from=deps /app/node_modules ./node_modules
COPY . .
RUN bun run build

FROM oven/bun:1-alpine AS runtime
WORKDIR /app
COPY --from=builder /app/.next ./.next
COPY --from=builder /app/node_modules ./node_modules
COPY --from=builder /app/package.json ./
USER nonroot
CMD ["bun", "run", "start"]
```

